Program: Great Lives
Title: Cyrus Todiwala on Dadabhai Naoroji
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07wby0q
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 30 Sep 2016
Chef Cyrus Todiwala chooses Dadabhai Naoroji, the 'Grand Old Man of India' who in 1892 became Britain's first Asian MP for Finsbury Central. He later returned to India and petitioned for the country to be self-governing. Ghandi, who was Dadabhai's mentee, would later refer to him as the Father of the Nation. Matthew Parris presents and Zerbanoo Gifford is the expert. Producer: Toby Field. Show less